<document>
	<title>Somatic cell genetic studies of cystic fibrosis.</title>

	<author>Mayo-B-J.</author>
	<author>Klebe-R-J.</author>
	<author>Lankford-B-J.</author>
	<author>Morris-N-R.</author>
	<author>Barnett-D-R.</author>
	<author>Bowman-B-H.</author>

	<source>Tex-Rep-Biol-Med. 1976. 34(1). P 107-11.</source>

	<abstract>The expression of the gene coding for the cystic fibrosis ciliary
   inhibitor has been examined in somatic cell hybrid clonal lines.
   Hybrids were produced by the fusion of cultured skin fibroblasts from
   cystic fibrosis patients with mouse RAG and LM (TK-) cell lines. The
   ciliary inhibitor was detected by the oyster ciliary assay in several
   primary hybrid clones but not detected in others, indicating the
   segregation of an associated nuclear gene.</abstract>

